<br>
I think the only thing he has to complain about is that mages aren't a 'cookie-cutter' class.<br>
<br>
Our tactics and play-style have to change considerably as we level up. The stuff I'm doing at 52 is very different than what I was able to do at 29, or 20. I know from reading these boards that my life will become different once again at 54 with a backstabbing pet, and radically change again at 56.<br>
<br>
As for the &lt;50 levels, if you're one level away from the next spell circle, you will rely on your nukes more than your pet. When you get to the next circle, your pet will be stronger, but your nukes will cost more mana, so you're back to depending on your pet. For a &lt;50 Mage, the most difficult time is just before the next spell circle.....<br>
<br>
We're unlike most other classes in Eq as to how we're played, which means we can be more difficult to level up if you're not willing to take the time to learn the class. <br>
<br>
You can't level a mage to 25 in the same solo spots where you levelled your monk/druid/wizzie/necro/sk to 25. Well, it may be possible, just not efficient. Most of those classes have their 'key' abilities by level 20. Our abilities change throughout our career.<br>
<br>
This is why, no matter how many improvements VI makes to the magician class, you won't see people running off to play mages in the same numbers in which people run off to create iksar monks.<br>
 <p>Naladini <BR>
Elementalist of the 52nd Season-Stormhammer<BR>
